Home Power is a bi-monthly American magazine. It is based in Ashland, Oregon. Circulation is greater than 100,000.
Published since 1987, Home Power has promoted a goal of reducing the use of fossil fuels for electricity generation by replacing fossil fuel generation capacity with currently available renewable electricity alternatives. Solar, wind, and hydro systems information is covered at a homeowner's do-it-yourself level with expert advice and examples. Home Power also promotes and presents information on energy efficient building and design practices. Electric vehicle information is also featured and its integration with renewable electricity systems and solar panels.


